248
00:15:29,880 --> 00:15:32,395
Well, Maseltov once again.

249
00:15:32,440 --> 00:15:36,957
And now Ros Lamb will be running
back down to our studios in London,

250
00:15:37,000 --> 00:15:40,710
so Ros, if you'd like to take
your di-tutetamine brohohibe.

251
00:15:40,760 --> 00:15:43,832
- And best of luck!
- (Squeaky voice) Thanks!

252
00:15:53,040 --> 00:15:55,032
(Jet engine rumbles)

253
00:15:55,080 --> 00:15:57,072
(Heartbeat)

254
00:16:07,280 --> 00:16:09,272
Dougal!

255
00:16:12,080 --> 00:16:15,278
And back to you, Peter,
at Shepherd's Bush.

256
00:16:32,520 --> 00:16:36,070
When the Olympics take place next
year in Swansea Industrial Park,

257
00:16:36,120 --> 00:16:38,715
there'll be a record number
of new events

258
00:16:38,760 --> 00:16:40,558
which have been formally accepted

259
00:16:40,600 --> 00:16:43,115
by the Olympic Committee
and Swansea Council.

260
00:16:43,160 --> 00:16:47,632
In fact there are a staggering
22 brand-new Olympic sports,

261
00:16:47,680 --> 00:16:51,151
but there's one sport
everyone wants to play.

262
00:16:51,200 --> 00:16:57,117
So Look Around You sent Pealy Maghti
off to our sister country, America,

263
00:16:57,160 --> 00:16:59,834
to try it out.

264
00:17:02,520 --> 00:17:04,512
(♪ Pounding rock music)

265
00:17:10,600 --> 00:17:13,320
(Pealy) Pennsylvania, USA.

266
00:17:13,360 --> 00:17:17,400
When you think of Pennsylvania,
you probably think of pencils.

267
00:17:17,440 --> 00:17:21,798
But in America, Pennsylvania
is best known for its baseball team,

268
00:17:21,840 --> 00:17:23,957
the Pennsylvania Pippins.

269
00:17:24,000 --> 00:17:25,992
And every Monday and Wednesday,

270
00:17:26,040 --> 00:17:30,557
thousands of fans flock to see such
baseball legends as TJ Nottingham,

271
00:17:30,600 --> 00:17:32,193
Sonny Thompson,

272
00:17:32,240 --> 00:17:34,596
and Xythantiops.

273
00:17:34,640 --> 00:17:38,520
But it's not just baseball that's
put Pennsylvania on the map.

274
00:17:38,560 --> 00:17:40,950
Jogging recently
became compulsory here,

275
00:17:41,000 --> 00:17:46,394
with stiff penalties for anyone who
doesn't fulfil the weekly mileage.

276
00:17:46,440 --> 00:17:48,671
But now,
there's a new sport in town,

277
00:17:48,720 --> 00:17:52,999
which may be about to take
the state, and the world, by storm.

278
00:17:53,040 --> 00:17:56,636
So I caught up with its inventor,
Scott Nolan.

279
00:17:56,680 --> 00:17:59,832
This sport you've created
isn't completely new, is it?

280
00:17:59,880 --> 00:18:02,031
Not exactly, Pealy, no.

281
00:18:02,080 --> 00:18:06,120
You see, I wanted to combine key
aspects of my two favourite sports,

282
00:18:06,160 --> 00:18:09,153
into a new hybrid, or combo-sport,

283
00:18:09,200 --> 00:18:10,998
which I believe has the potential

284
00:18:11,040 --> 00:18:14,272
to become the most exciting
spectator sport at the Olympics.

285
00:18:14,320 --> 00:18:16,755
What are the two sports
that you've combined?

286
00:18:16,800 --> 00:18:19,190
Tennis and golf.

287
00:18:19,240 --> 00:18:23,200
Well, I'm dying to try it out.
Now, am I dressed for the occasion?

288
00:18:23,240 --> 00:18:26,039
I hope so, let's see,
you've got the shoes and the socks,

289
00:18:26,080 --> 00:18:28,436
the pants, the hat...

290
00:18:28,480 --> 00:18:31,951
All you need is this...
and you're all set!

291
00:18:35,640 --> 00:18:37,632
Let's play gonnis!

292
00:18:40,760 --> 00:18:43,673
Gonnis is a perfect mixture
of golf and tennis.

293
00:18:45,080 --> 00:18:46,719
The rules are very simple -

294
00:18:46,760 --> 00:18:50,720
get the ball over the net, onto the
green and into your opponent's hole,

295
00:18:50,760 --> 00:18:54,231
whilst avoiding the bunkers
and the water hazard.

296
00:18:54,280 --> 00:18:58,240
The game was overseen by the world's
only professional gonnis umpire,

297
00:18:58,280 --> 00:19:01,990
Bunny Gnowles, who also happens
to be Scott's boyfriend.

298
00:19:02,040 --> 00:19:05,238
- Go easy on me, Scott!
- Not a chance!

299
00:19:09,720 --> 00:19:12,918
With its classy blend
of elegance and style,

300
00:19:12,960 --> 00:19:15,998
gonnis has become the game of choice
for the jet set,

301
00:19:16,040 --> 00:19:20,319
with such players as Manhattan Dave
and the Shah of Israel,

302
00:19:20,360 --> 00:19:23,751
and Scott even had an order
for 40,000 gonnis sets

303
00:19:23,800 --> 00:19:26,998
from none other than Tony Curtis.

304
00:19:29,800 --> 00:19:31,598
Quiet, please!

305
00:19:31,640 --> 00:19:33,074
Birdie-love.

306
00:19:33,120 --> 00:19:36,318
- I'm getting the hang of this!
- We'll see about that.

307
00:19:40,480 --> 00:19:42,915
Out! Quiet, please!

308
00:19:42,960 --> 00:19:44,440
Eagle - 15.

309
00:19:44,480 --> 00:19:46,472
(Softly) Come on, Scott, come on.

310
00:19:54,160 --> 00:19:56,880
- Advantage, Miss Maghti.
- Go on, Pealy!

311
00:19:56,920 --> 00:19:58,877
- Quiet, please!
- Go on, Pealy!

312
00:19:58,920 --> 00:20:02,072
Tensions ran high,
both on and off the court.

313
00:20:02,120 --> 00:20:04,351
Ma'am, did you not hear me
say "quiet" then?

314
00:20:04,400 --> 00:20:06,551
It's (bleep) off-putting
to the players,

315
00:20:06,600 --> 00:20:10,150
it's (bleep) off-putting to the
opponent who you're not rooting for,

316
00:20:10,200 --> 00:20:12,431
it's a (bleep) for him and for me!

317
00:20:12,480 --> 00:20:15,837
And if you continue, I'm gonna
(bleep) remove you from the court.

318
00:20:15,880 --> 00:20:18,076
Do you understand? Thank you.

319
00:20:19,240 --> 00:20:21,357
(Bleep)

320
00:20:22,680 --> 00:20:25,240
Miss Maghti, you are four under par.

321
00:20:28,800 --> 00:20:32,794
Finally, it was time for me to put
my putting skills to the test.

322
00:20:35,000 --> 00:20:37,959
- (Woman) Go on, Pealy!
- (Bleep)

323
00:20:41,720 --> 00:20:44,189
Hole, set and match, Pealy Maghti.

324
00:20:44,240 --> 00:20:48,678
I'd done it! Against all odds, I'd
beaten the American at his own game.

325
00:20:48,720 --> 00:20:52,031
- That was fantastic!
- Yes, beginner's luck.

326
00:20:53,880 --> 00:20:57,510
Miss Maghti, congratulations.
You played a good game.

327
00:20:58,920 --> 00:21:00,479
Quiet, please.

328
00:21:01,520 --> 00:21:03,113
Quiet, please.

329
00:21:03,160 --> 00:21:05,391
Where now for Scott Nolan?

330
00:21:05,440 --> 00:21:08,592
I'm developing another combo-sport
at the moment.

331
00:21:08,640 --> 00:21:10,871
Again, it's a mixture
of two other sports -

332
00:21:10,920 --> 00:21:12,752
fencing and darts.

333
00:21:19,320 --> 00:21:21,596
Gosh, you were really good
at gonnis!

334
00:21:21,640 --> 00:21:25,600
Thanks. And the funny thing is, I've
never played golf or tennis before.

335
00:21:25,640 --> 00:21:28,758
- And I was on my period.
- Obviously a natural.

336
00:21:28,800 --> 00:21:31,759
- Yes, well done, Pealy.
- Yeah, well played.

337
00:21:31,800 --> 00:21:34,440
- Thanks, chaps.
- That is a beautiful trophy.

338
00:21:38,720 --> 00:21:42,794
Well, we're just waiting for
Ros Lamb to speed into the studio

339
00:21:42,840 --> 00:21:44,718
all the way from Aberdeen,

340
00:21:44,760 --> 00:21:48,037
and I believe she should be here
any second now.

341
00:21:51,560 --> 00:21:54,519
Well, while we're waiting
for Ros, erm...

342
00:21:54,560 --> 00:21:58,918
Oh, and I believe we're now seeing
outside Television Centre,

343
00:21:58,960 --> 00:22:03,079
where Ros Lamb should be speeding
into view any second now.

344
00:22:03,120 --> 00:22:06,431
Erm, Jack, I believe you used to
go out with Ros Lamb, didn't you?

345
00:22:06,480 --> 00:22:08,472
(Jack) Yes,
it was several years ago

346
00:22:08,520 --> 00:22:11,592
